title: Drinks
text: Sat on the second level deck looking at the water while enjoying happy hour. Live music several night a week. We did not eat.
place: Mulligan's Beach House Bar and Grill

title: Wonderful!
text: We enjoyed a beautiful meal with great wine and excellent service while sitting outside and watching the world go by. Lovely evening.

title: Appetizer and wine
text: We stopped after our boat tour for peel and eat shrimp and a glass of wine. Beautiful view and really good shrimp.

title: Drinks!
text: We stopped for drinks on the deck and it was wonderful. A great way to relax on a sunny afternoon. Service was great. Didn’t have any food.

title: Good location
text: The service was excellent but the food only ok. My fish tastes like something I would prepare at home, which isn’t saying much.

title: Good Food and Wine
text: Enjoyed a couple of bottles of wine and good food on the patio with friends. Gluten free options available.

title: Great Deck
text: We love to sit by the water while having a good meal and this fit the bill exactly. Right on the beach.

title: What a Burger!!
text: Can’t remember ever having such a goo burger! Juicy with yummy toppings. I had the jalapeño popper burger and it was amazing.

title: Great Carry Out
text: The pizza we ordered was very good and prepared quickly. They have a lot of unusual combinations and gluten-free crust as well. So nice to take it back to your hotel and put your feet while you eat.

title: Interesting
text: We really enjoyed the visit to this amazing historic site. The guides are well-informed and it’s astonishing how well-preserved it is. The drive in does require about 6 miles of dirt road which is not in the best shape. We drove it slowly in a MINI and did fine, however, my car dropped red dust for days afterward.

title: So beautiful!
text: What a wonderful drive on a sunny day...especially in a convertible! Beautiful views around every curve and well worth the time.

title: Stunning!!
text: Such a beautiful church incorporated right into the gorgeous scenery. It was very crowded on a sunny Saturday, but they had people directing traffic and it all went well. Definitely worth a visit, even with the crowds.

title: Great Stay
text: We had a great room with two queens, a sofa and fireplace, plus a balcony overlooking the pool and beautiful scenery. It was very clean and comfortable. The staff was very helpful and the breakfast delicious. Couldn’t have asked for more.

title: Really Great Class
text: We had so much fun, learned a lot, and ate great food. Even though I worked on only a couple of the recipes, the chef was careful to draw our attention to tips he was giving to other students as they worked on their dishes. Definitely would recommend to someone who is not a chef, but wants to improve their cooking skills.

title: Fun...but
text: It was very informative and the food was really great. However, I am not a good cook which is one of the reasons I signed up for the class, and I feel the only thing I could make again with confidence is the recipe I worked on in class. For example, while reviewing the other recipes after arriving home, I had a lot of questions on how to deal with tomatillos as well as dried and roasted peppers...a few things we don’t cook with on a regular basis in the Midwest.

title: Good Specials
text: We enjoyed the choices of beer and hard cider, and the specials we ordered were very good. The ribs from the regular menu were ok, but disappointing because they were only ok. They were a letdown after everything else being so good.

title: Breakfast!
text: Really yummy breakfast with GREAT coffee. The only downside to this place is the very limited parking.

title: Drive-through
text: When you want quick, New Mexican food, but you don’t want to get dressed, drive through Bumble Bee’s. Enjoy at home!

title: No Tequila!
text: The food and service at this restaurant are both very good, but they don’t have a full liquor license so the margaritas are made with agave wine instead of tequila. They’re not bad, but now quite the same.

title: Good Margaritas
text: The food, service, and margaritas were all very good. Our only objection was it was somewhat hard to know what we were eating because everything ran together on the plate.

title: Love it!
text: My daughter is an organic farmer, so of course we had to check out the market on our last visit. It is a great market with a good variety of food and crafts. One of the best I’ve seen.

title: Beautiful
text: Very pretty historic church. I was especially fascinated by the old section that had been incorporated into the “new” church.
place: The Cathedral Basilica of St. Francis of Assisi

title: Very creative
text: This is a must see at least one time just because it is so crazy creative. And crazy is an operative word. It’s hard to describe, and while you may not like the artwork, you won’t be bored.

title: Historic
text: Very interesting and historic square with lots of shops, restaurants and people. Enjoyed wandering around and looking at the local crafts and fine art galleries.

title: Beautiful
text: A beautifully, well-preserved chapel that is worth the admission price just to see the amazing staircase which boggles the mind.

title: Outstanding!
text: Had lunch at Pasqual’s and it was one of the best meals I had in Santa Fe. Fresh and well-prepared with cheerful, fast service. It’s easy to see why this place is so popular. AND the freshly made gluten-free bread is unbelievably good.

title: Good in a pinch
text: Someone told us we MUST stop here on our way to Ghost Ranch. After reading the reviews I really expected more. They seem to carry a little bit of everything, but it’s just a store. Not worth a stop unless you need something.

title: Beautiful Location
text: We made a day visit to Ghost Ranch and really enjoyed both the drive there and the hike to Chimney Rock. The scenery is beautiful. It’s easy to see how an artist could be inspired living there.

title: Fascinating!
text: What a wonderful look into a piece of ancient American history you won’t see anywhere else. The guide was knowledgeable and gave a good overview of life in the cliff dwellings.

title: Amazing View
text: We enjoyed a very nice dinner here with a wonderful view of the Acropolis lit up at night. There was only one gluten-free main course option, and while it was very good, I prefer more choices. Also, because of the way they had our table set up, I took a fall when getting up from my chair. There is a raised platform against the wall and they set the table lengthwise along that platform so four people in our party had the back of their chair just a foot or so away from the step down. I missed the step getting up and fell on my a**. People have broken bones on less, so be careful if you get that table!

title: Excellent Lunch
text: The food and service were top notch, plus it is a very relaxing place for a late lunch and an adult beverage.

title: Wonderful Lunch
text: Really great food with an amazing view of the Acropolis from the rooftop. Anna was delightful to chat with while she gave us very attentive service.

title: Must See
text: Yes it’s crowded, but no picture can depict the grandeur of this historic site. You have to be there to really take it all in.

title: Terrible Service!
text: The manager at our hotel recommended this place to us and made our reservation. One would think that the restaurant would want to continue to get these types of referrals, but we had such poor service that clearly they don’t care. The food was very good, and the atmosphere in the outdoor space lovely, but my husband actually had to get up from the table and interrupt a waiter from playing on his phone at ask for menus. It didn’t improve the rest of the evening. It’s not as though we were in a hurry, but every step of the process required us waving someone down.
place: By The Glass wine bar & bistrot

title: Stunning!
text: This is a very interesting, historic and beautiful setting for a restaurant. We enjoyed a wonderful evening on the rooftop terrace and had an outstanding dinner. The service was good, the food excellent and the view lovely. The indoor dinning spaces look cozy and inviting as well.

title: Delicious!
text: A group of ten of us enjoyed an excellent meal at this lovely rooftop restaurant. The service was good and the portions so large we could have shared some of the main courses. The ribs are excellent, but enough for two unless you are a really big eater.

title: Nice Lunch
text: The weather was great so we wanted to eat outside and watch the world go by. The food was very good and plentiful, and the atmosphere relaxing. I recommend the lamb kabobs.

title: Stunning
text: An easy visit that costs a suggested one euro to enter and is wonderful to see, especially if you are a church lover like me. You can spend a little time here, or a lot, depending on how involved you want to get with the history. Definitely stop by!

title: Loved It!
text: Yes there is walking (uphill like all of Lake Como) and yes there are some strange artifacts in the collection, but the property alone is worth a visit. It is truly beautiful and the views are stunning. We walked uphill to arrive, and took the water taxi back for the views. If you take the boat to Como you will get the same views and even if you do the water taxi both directions you will still have stairs and hills to climb from the landing, but less than walking up from Lenno.

title: Good for Lunch
text: Quiet and relaxing atmosphere by the pool with attentive service and good food. We were doing a walking tour of Bellagio and wanted to eat NOW. Passed this place and decided to give it a try. It was enjoyable.

title: Wonderful!
text: Lovely atmosphere, attentive service, wonderful food...the perfect dinner in Bellagio. Our waiter was kind and helpful in selecting a gluten-free item. There are some interesting offerings on the menu and we enjoyed our meal here.

title: Wonderful Veiw
text: The food was very good but much like all other restaurants with good food in Italy. However, the view was amazing and we really enjoyed watching the moon rise over the lake. Other-worldly. Gluten free options available.
place: Ristorante La Terrazza Lago di Como

title: Clean room
text: A clean place to lay your head but nothing special. About 15 minutes out from downtown. Coffee available but only those terrible fake sugary flavored “creamers” to put in it. Real cream please!! Packaged bars and such for breakfast but nothing gluten-free. Hairdryers available at the front desk.
place: Extended Stay America - Fort Wayne - North

title: Open on Sunday
text: Stopped here for lunch on our way through town because it seemed everything else was closed on Sunday. The food was ok but the service very slow. They also charge for refills on iced tea! Who does that anymore?

title: Happy Hour!
text: Happy Hour is from 4-6pm and includes the little exhibit about the building. I enjoyed the exhibit, but it was definitely better to pay $10.50 to go to the bar and enjoy a beverage while enjoying the view than to pay $20 for the exhibit and view alone.

title: Fun!
text: Yes this is a touristy thing to do, but my husband and I enjoyed seeing it and reading the signs explaining the history. You should go once.

title: Very Good
text: We hesitated to stop because of some iffy reviews we saw but it turned out to be very good. The food was excellent and the service friendly. The atmosphere is a little tatty but it is still a fun stop.

title: Delicious!
text: We were attacked to this restaurant because we like Middle Eastern food AND they have gluten-free options. This is absolutely the best Middle Eastern food I’ve tasted in a restaurant outside the Middle East. Very good service as well.

title: Excellent Lunch
text: Really good salads and outstanding, friendly service. What more could you ask for? Gluten free options available.

title: So good!
text: This place would get a “5” if the service was better. There were only about 4 other tables occupied when we were there, yet the wait for food was long. Otherwise it was really, really good!

title: Star Wars come to life!
text: If you are lucky enough to visit when the military are doing training exercises, you will have the thrill of a lifetime; otherwise it’s just another really beautiful canyon.

title: Interesting
text: One of the many weird and unusual sites to see in Death Valley. We walked about a mile on the salt flats and felt like we were on a Star Trek set.

title: Really Beautiful!
text: Definitely worth the drive to see the beautiful views. We drove it close to dusk and the colors were amazing. Maybe not the same at other times of the day, or maybe even better; but definitely worth the trip.

title: So. Much. Fun.
text: I can’t believe that I go to Las Vegas every year and have never been to this fun, fun place! My 34 year-old son wanted to go because he is a pinball geek and we had so much fun for just $10 each. I really love the old machines that cost just a quarter or two, and he loved it all. Will definitely be back on my next visit.

title: Quick Tour
text: You will see only the first floor of the house and there are no pictures allowed; but the guide was very good and did a nice job of pointing out features of the building, the art collection and the fascinating story of James Williams.

title: Lovely Stroll
text: This is a really beautiful park that embodies the very essence of Savannah. The fountain and monument are worth a visit.

title: A little disappointing
text: An interesting place to stop because of its movie history but the food was only ok...not bad but nothing special. The service was very good though.

title: Truly Beautiful
text: If you love traditional churches this one is not to be missed, but be aware of Mass times before you go because they close the church to touring at least half an hour before Mass begins. You can’t even quietly walk around and pray at the different windows before Mass. That is “touring.”
place: Cathedral of St. John the Baptist

title: Hidden Treasure
text: This tiny place gave us a big (and pleasant) surprise. It’s a little out of the way, but worth the effort to get there. The food was delicious and the service friendly and very attractive. Gluten-free and vegan options available.
